<TrainingDetailsVTwo ID="x18259" Name="Facebook" Layout="default-training_v2.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Facebook Integration</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">A full-width banner image that rotates between all included images.</Abstract><IsTrainingHomePage type="boolean" label="Is this the training homepage?" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</IsTrainingHomePage><TrainingImage type="imagefile" label="Page Type Image" hidden="false" readonly="false" required="false" Expanded="true" AlternateText="" Border="" HSpace="" VSpace="" Width="417" Height="292" Alignment="">Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Element Views/Facebook Setup.png</TrainingImage><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<strong></strong>Imports status updates from Facebook directly into your page.
<h3>Proper Use</h3>
<p>&nbsp;This is a simple feature to use in our system. Provided that you have a Facebook page for your department, simply enter the Facebook ID number and how many messages you want to show. When users view the page, the latest messages are pulled directly from Facebook. If you leave the ID blank, then this feature is not displayed on the page.</p>
<p>To effectively use this feature, you must pursue a social media strategy! This takes dedicated, frequent attention to your Facebook community. What good are these status messages if they don't change or meet students' needs?</p>
<h3>Finding Your Facebook ID</h3>
<p>There are two ways that you can find your facebook ID. The easiest way is to locate it in URL of your browser when you are on your page (you do not have to be logged in). In the URL you will see a number between 12 and 16 characters.</p>
<p><img alt="finding your facebook ID" height="346" src="Images/Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Components/facebookID.jpg" width="488" /></p>
<p>If you do not see any numbers in your browser URL hover your mouse over your profile picture. At the bottom of your browser you will see a link. This link will contain your facebook ID.</p>
<h3>Facebook Access Token</h3>
<p>If your Facebook configuration area includes an "Access_Token" field, that is no longer required and you can leave that element empty.</p>
